						<h3 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-[#111827] mb-4">5. Processing of minors' personal data</h3>

						<h4 class="text-xl font-semibold text-[#111827] mb-3 mt-6">5.1. Age of consent</h4>
						<p class="mb-4">
							In Portugal, the minimum age for a minor to give valid consent to the processing of personal data in connection with information society services is 13 years (Article 16 of Law No. 58/2019). Where a user is under 13, processing of their personal data is only lawful with the consent of the holder of parental responsibility, which We collect and verify through email confirmation sent to the adult at the time of registration.
						</p>
						<p class="mb-4">
							Where a user is 13 or older, they may give consent themselves; however, as a contractual condition of access to the App under our Terms &amp; Conditions, all users under 18 must use the App with the knowledge and consent of a parent or legal guardian, verified through the same email confirmation process.
						</p>
						<p>
							Where data concerning health is shared through the chat, processing is based on explicit consent, given by the user aged 13 or over and/or by the holder of parental responsibility, as applicable.
						</p>

						<h4 class="text-xl font-semibold text-[#111827] mb-3 mt-6">5.2. Age verification</h4>
						<p>
							At registration, users are required to provide their date of birth. This information is used to determine the applicable consent requirements and to restrict access to age-appropriate content and features. Users aged 16 to 18 may have access to content or features not available to users aged 12 to 15.
						</p>

						<h4 class="text-xl font-semibold text-[#111827] mb-3 mt-6">5.3. Parental rights</h4>
						<p>
							If You are the parent or legal guardian of a minor who has provided personal data without proper consent, You may contact us using the details in Section 2 to request its removal.
						</p>
